RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 9000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $4,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAMA'S PROUD JOKE stalked three to four wide, dropped back in the far turn, closed gamely late, and got up in the final strides. SPIRIT RACER crossed over to the two path, showed the way through the far turn, saw margins decrease into the stretch, and was caught late. WIZARDOFMENLOPARK sat in range from between foes, chased the leader through the stretch and flattened out. ZURI RISASI lagged early, advanced inside, and improved late stretch. CLEVER CONNECTION stalked inside, and wilted into the stretch. EXPLICIT FIRE was outrun then eased, and walked off. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of CLEVER CONNECTION against the rider of WIZARDOFMENLOPARK alleging interference in the stretch run was not allowed. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of CLEVER CONNECTION against the rider of SPIRIT RACER alleging interference in the backstretch was not allowed.

ENTRY.NAME: Mama's Proud Joke
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3-4w, dropped back, closed gamely, up late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Lesser Claiming Races For $6,000 (AB $8,000 ) Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JULIUS THE GREAT broke sharply to set the early pace, responded to a looming threat from PRESS GANG, and just held after a long hard drive. PRESS GANG sat just off the leader in the four path, moved up menacingly near the quarter pole, was all out under heavy urging but was unable to get by after determined effort. YORKTOWN sat in the three path in striking position, chased inside but was no threat to the top two leaders and held show. PERDITION went wide through the backstretch, and was unable to improve position through the stretch. FROBISHER BAY lagged early and offered little. DREADNAUGHT saved inside and lacked a stretch response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRINKING AGAIN chased four to five wide, steadied midstretch and drove clear. LINCHPIN STORM sped to the front to secure a rail position, drifted out midstretch bothering IMPACTO and finished evenly. DANCING WILLIE raced in close quarters early, circled the field into the lane, and closed gradually outside. IMPACTO rated wide off the pace, fanned four-wide leaving the backstretch, went in pursuit of the leader, moved up menacingly in the final furlong then was squeezed out and finished well. BACKSTREET BOBBY chased inside, and improved position late. AWHITESPORTSCOAT trailed the field, and rallied belatedly. SMARTY RIVER PANTS vied between and lacked a closing response. ISLE OF SKYE sat in striking distance while five wide, and gave way in stretch. STEWARDS INQUIRY and JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection was lodged by the rider of IMPACTO against the riders of LINCHPIN STORM and DRINKING AGAIN alleging interference in the stretch run. After review by the Board of Stewards LINCHPIN STORM was disqualified and placed fourth for interference with IMPACTO. The objection against DRINKING AGAIN was disallowed.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DECOY unhurried early, shifted outside near the five-sixteenth pole, was brushed at the head of the lane, swept the lead and won going away. MIDNITE CHILL assumed the lead while five wide, moved clear nearing the quarter pole, was overtaken midstretch while showing signs of tiring, and finished up second best. SILVERFOOT hurried away, fanned four-wide leaving the backstretch, drifted out brushing DECOY, shifted outside entering the stretch and closed under encouragement to secure a show placing. ALL THAT GOLD stalked from the rail, chased into the stretch, and wilted. H K MELODY stalked four-wide, and had no response when called upon.
